  <!-- Section: Common Mistakes -->
  <section id="mistakes" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insurance Below €100,000 Minimum</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta explicitly requires €100,000 minimum coverage for EU, UK, and Malta. Budget nomad insurance often falls short. Verify coverage amounts in writing before applying—don't assume your existing policy qualifies.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Including Passive Income in Calculations</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Malta only counts professional income—salary, freelance fees, business income. Dividends, rental income, interest, and capital gains don't count toward the €3,500/month requirement. Ensure your professional income alone meets the threshold.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Failing the 5-Month Minimum Stay</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Unlike some nomad visas, Malta requires genuine residence—5 months per year minimum. If you're a heavy traveler, track your days carefully. Falling short means renewal denial. Consider if Malta's residency requirement fits your lifestyle.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Insufficient Future Income Proof</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">You need contracts showing €17,500 income over the next 5 months—not just historical bank statements. Freelancers must have signed agreements or letters of intent. Vague "ongoing client relationships" may not suffice.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Expecting Permanent Residency Path</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Nomad Residence Permit maxes out at 4 years and does not lead to permanent residency or citizenship. If long-term settlement is your goal, consider other visa categories or countries with PR pathways.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

